                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 France/835</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        President-elect <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-30">January 30,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Governor</hi>: This will acknowledge your telegram of
                    January twenty-seventh with regard to the French situation.</p>
                <p>In view of the informal suggestions which have already been made by Ambassador
                    Edge urging the December fifteenth payment, which I described to you by
                    telephone, I understand that you do not think it advisable to send any further
                    communication to the French. I shall act accordingly.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
